Seven suspects have been arrested following a cash-in transit heist on the N2 between Qumbu and Tsolo in the Eastern Cape. Earlier two were apprehended after a shootout between police and suspects. A motorist was shot dead in the crossfire. In the East of Johannesburg, five more suspects were caught after crime intelligence followed them. A Toyota Hilux was retrieved along with three firearms and bags of cash. The arrests follow the formation of a task team to curb cash-in-transit heists which have escalated in the last few months. Police are still searching for others who may be involved. Click below for related video: 